The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Damon is a father again
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Damon is a father again
                              Doing great                            
	Los Angeles, Aug. 21 (Reuters): Actor Matt Damon and his wife welcomed their second daughter into the world yesterday, and all were doing great, his spokeswoman said.        
	She is a healthy, beautiful baby girl, spokeswoman Jennifer Allen told Reuters in an email. The couple named their daughter Gia Zavala Damon, but no other details were released.        
	Damon, 37, star of the Bourne action movies, and his wife, Luciana, 32, already have one daughter named Isabella, who was born in 2006. Luciana has another daughter from a previous marriage. Damon had several small movie roles in the early 1990s, but saw his Hollywood breakthrough in 1997s Good Will Hunting playing a young janitor and mathematics genius.                                                                                                                                                                            
